channel.title: What are you looking forward to this year?
channel.description:
I was just reading [url='https://movies.ign.com/articles/114/1142532p1.html']this article[/url] about some movies coming out this year, and while there's plenty I have no desire to watch, there's also a lot that look awesome, or at least fun. So I just thought I'd see what other people are anticipating.
What are [b]you[/b] looking forward to this year? What movies are you pumped for? What games are coming out that you can't wait to get your hands on?
For me:
After watching the trailer for Battle: Los Angeles, I gotta say I really want to see it. Super 8, being a J.J. Abrams flick, deserves at least one viewing. Hoping for more Star Trek than Cloverfield. Cowboys and Aliens...Daniel Craig and Harrison Ford are gonna make me go see it. It's a strange premise but I've seen stranger turn out great. I'm also cautiously optimistic about Transformers, Pirates, and X-Men. I'm hoping they can turn their franchises around from their previous entries, but I'm prepared for disappointment. Thor, Drive, Source Code, and Apollo 18...will wait for reviews.
Games wise, Portal 2 is almost here, and then I can't think of anything until ME3 and Skyrim in holiday season. Here's hoping we get some surprise releases this year too *wink wink nudge nudge*
